# CleanMateX Flutter No Code Generation Rules

## Core Principle
All code must be explicit, readable, and fully visible.

No hidden code.
No generated code.
No magic.

## Forbidden Tools / Packages
Do NOT use:
- freezed
- json_serializable
- built_value
- mobx_codegen
- injectable generators
- any code generator that creates hidden runtime or mapping behavior
- any generator that requires build_runner for models, unions, DI, or serialization

If a package requires build_runner, reject it unless explicitly approved by the project owner.

## Forbidden Patterns
- No `.g.dart` files
- No `part 'model.g.dart';`
- No `part 'model.freezed.dart';`
- No `@JsonSerializable()`
- No `@freezed`
- No generated unions / sealed-state code
- No hidden mapping logic
- No annotation-driven model generation
- No hidden DI registration generation

## Required Alternative
All models must be written manually.

Every model should manually include, where needed:
- constructor
- fromJson
- toJson
- copyWith
- equality
- toString

## Equality Rule
Manual equality is acceptable.
Using `equatable` is acceptable.
Do not use generated equality tools.

## Cursor Behavior
Cursor must:
- NEVER suggest freezed
- NEVER suggest json_serializable
- NEVER suggest build_runner
- NEVER generate `.g.dart` files
- ALWAYS write full manual model implementations
- ALWAYS include explicit fromJson / toJson / copyWith when needed
- ALWAYS keep mapping logic visible in source code

If code generation is suggested, reject it and rewrite manually.

## Rationale
We choose manual code because it gives:
- easier debugging
- no hidden behavior
- better AI code generation consistency
- fewer version conflicts
- easier onboarding and maintenance
- full control over parsing logic
- less toolchain friction

## Accepted Trade-off
- Slightly more boilerplate
- More typing

This trade-off is acceptable because transparency and control are more important for this project than reducing a small amount of boilerplate.

## Model Style Guidance
When creating manual models:
- validate types explicitly
- handle nulls intentionally
- convert num to double safely
- keep JSON keys explicit
- avoid dynamic usage spreading across code
- prefer small focused helper parsing functions when repeated

## Anti-Patterns to Reject
Reject:
- models that rely on generated parts
- hidden serializers
- annotation-based magic
- generated copyWith
- generated unions for state classes
- generated service locators